<Layout
  title="Send Money from Brazil to Japan — BRL to JPY Transfer Guide"
  description="Everything about sending money from Brazil to Japan. Compare BRL to JPY rates and services. Essential guide for the Nikkei community and Japanese-Brazilians sending money to Japan."
  keywords="Brazil to Japan remittance, BRL to JPY, send money Brazil Japan, Nikkei remittance, Japanese Brazilian money transfer, Brasil Japão remessa, BRL JPY exchange rate"
  image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2506923/pexels-photo-2506923.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1200&h=630&fit=crop"
  type="website"
>
  <RemittancePage
    flag="🇯🇵"
    countryEn="Japan"
    countryZh="日本"
    currencyCode="JPY"
    currencyNameEn="Japanese Yen"
    currencyNameZh="日元"
    rate="25.8 JPY"
    externalHref="https://www.pandaremit.com/en/bra/send-money-to-japan"
    heroImage="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2506923/pexro-photo-2506923.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600&h=600&fit=crop"
    overviewEn="Brazil and Japan share one of the most unique cultural connections in the world. Brazil is home to approximately 1.5 million people of Japanese descent — the largest Japanese diaspora community outside Japan itself — known as the Nikkei community. This deep cultural bond has created a consistent and significant remittance corridor between the two countries. Money flows in both directions: Brazilian Nikkei workers in Japan (known as dekasegi) send money back to Brazil, while Brazilian families send money to support relatives studying or working in Japan."
    overviewZh="巴西和日本共享着世界上最独特的文化纽带之一。巴西拥有约150万日裔人口——日本本土以外最大的日本侨民社区——被称为日裔巴西人（Nikkei）社区。这一深厚的文化纽带在两国之间创造了持续且重要的汇款走廊。资金双向流动：在日本工作的巴西日裔工人（称为dekasegi）向巴西汇款，而巴西家庭则向在日本留学或工作的亲属汇款。"
    tip1En="JPY moves in large numbers: The Japanese Yen is typically traded in hundreds or thousands per major currency unit. Don't be alarmed by large JPY amounts — 10,000 JPY is approximately R$390."
    tip1Zh="日元数字较大：日元通常以数百或数千的单位与主要货币兑换。不必对大额日元数字感到惊讶——10,000日元约等于390雷亚尔。"
    tip2En="Consider the dekasegi corridor: Many services specialize in Brazil-Japan transfers due to high demand from the Nikkei community. These specialized services often have better rates for this corridor."
    tip2Zh="考虑dekasegi走廊：由于日裔巴西人社区需求旺盛，许多服务专注于巴西-日本汇款走廊。这些专业服务通常对此走廊提供更好的汇率。"
    tip3En="Japan Post Bank is widely used: Many recipients in Japan prefer transfers to Japan Post Bank (Yucho Bank), which is accessible even in rural areas. Verify your recipient's preferred receiving institution."
    tip3Zh="日本邮政银行被广泛使用：日本的许多收款人更倾向于转账至日本邮政银行（郵貯銀行），即使在农村地区也可访问。请确认收款人偏好的接收机构。"
    communityEn="The Japanese-Brazilian community (Nikkei) is deeply woven into Brazilian society, particularly in São Paulo state where the majority live. Many Nikkei Brazilians maintain dual cultural identities and strong connections to Japan. The phenomenon of dekasegi — Nikkei Brazilians working in Japanese factories and sending remittances home — has been a significant social and economic feature since the late 1980s."
    communityZh="日裔巴西人（Nikkei）社区深深融入巴西社会，尤其是在大多数人居住的圣保罗州。许多日裔巴西人保持着双重文化认同，并与日本保持着深厚联系。dekasegi现象——日裔巴西人在日本工厂工作并向家乡汇款——自1980年代末以来一直是重要的社会和经济特征。"
    regulatoryEn="Japan has strict anti-money laundering regulations enforced by the Financial Services Agency (FSA). All remittance providers must be registered in Japan. Transfers from Brazil must comply with Banco Central do Brasil requirements. Japan allows up to JPY 1 million per transfer without enhanced documentation for personal transfers; larger amounts require proof of purpose."
    regulatoryZh="日本拥有由金融厅（FSA）执行的严格反洗钱法规。所有汇款提供商必须在日本注册。来自巴西的转账必须符合巴西中央银行的要求。日本允许个人转账每笔最多100万日元无需增强文件证明；更大金额需要提供目的证明。"
    transferTime="2–4 days"
    minAmount="R$100"
    maxAmount="R$80,000"
  />
</Layout>
